
README for Random Sentence Generator

To run the program, use a command like the following:

      java RandomSentenceGenerator < Poem.g


This directory contains:

1. Definition.java: keeps info about one non-terminal

2. DefinitionTable.java: maps strings to definitions

3. RandomSentenceGenerator.java: reads in grammar from standard input
     and prints out random sentences.

4. Sample Grammar Files:

     Poem.g
     Extension-request.g
     Haiku.g  
     College-rejection-letter.g  
     StarTrek-episode.g

  These were written by a number of people, including Karl Brown,
  Lucas Ryan, Garret Kaminga, and other unsuspecting individuals.  Feel
  free to write your own grammars as well...

